This paper is about improving the training of deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a new method for improving the training of deep neural networks. The second most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper specifically mentions experiments on convolutional neural networks. The third most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper is about improving the performance of deep learning models. The fourth most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper is about improving the training of neural networks. The fifth most likely category is cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), as the paper also discusses the implications of the proposed method on hardware design for deep learning accelerators.
